(61, 'Evolution is partly to blame for our obsession with Brangelina', 'In fact, our brains adapted long ago to be deeply interested in the beautiful and famous among us, says Daniel Kruger, a psychologist at the University of Michigan. Just consider our close relative, the monkey.', '2016-09-24 18:00:09', '0', 0, 0, 'http://www.theverge.com/2016/9/24/13037106/angelina-jolie-brad-pitt-divorce-science-gossip-evolution', 'http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/8RCCEtmak9_5Bdv0Km6Z7Q--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en-US/homerun/verge.vox.com/e8fe5ad1f9a60bb3fee36d98d28315e6', 2),
(62, 'How science fiction has imagined colonizing our solar system and beyond', 'Next week, Elon Musk is slated to make a big announcement about SpaceX’s most ambitious goal to date: the colonization of Mars. Musk has never shied away from the science fictional aspects of his ventures, and it’s a very safe assumption that genre works have played some role in his outlook on the world. Colonization in particular has been a long-standing part of science fiction, whether it’s an explicit goal of the story or not.', '2016-09-24 17:00:09', '0', 0, 0, 'http://www.theverge.com/2016/9/24/12999798/science-fiction-mars-spacex-outer-space-colonization-theories', 'http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/w.wizh2uQoQUR7rd4A.hjw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_US/News/The%20Verge/wesshar.gif', 2),
